<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7269] Make CqlInputFormat and CqlRecordReader consistent with comments</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7269</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Both the CqlInputFormat and CqlPagingInputFormat have the following comment:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;/**
...
 *   the number of CQL rows per page
 *   CQLConfigHelper.setInputCQLPageRowSize. The &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt; page row size is 1000. You 
 *   should set it to &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;as big as possible, but no bigger.&quot;&lt;/span&gt; It set the LIMIT &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; the CQL 
 *   query, so you need set it big enough to minimize the network overhead, and also
 *   not too big to avoid out of memory issue.
...
**/
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The property is used in both classes, but the default is only set to 1000 in CqlPagingRecordReader explicitly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should either make the default part of the CqlConfigHelper so it&apos;s set in both places or update the comments in the CqlInputFormat to say that if it&apos;s not set, it will default to the java driver fetch size which is 5000.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
